## Step 2 — Set up environment variables

    cp .env.example .env.local

Open .env.local and fill in the values.

### Generate BETTER_AUTH_SECRET

You need a secure random string. Run one of these:

    Windows PowerShell:
    [System.Convert]::ToBase64String((1..32|ForEach{[byte](Get-Random -Max 256)}))

    Mac or Linux:
    openssl rand -base64 32

Copy the output and paste it as the value of BETTER_AUTH_SECRET.
{{if .HasGitHub}}
### GitHub OAuth

1. Go to https://github.com/settings/applications/new
2. Application name: {{.ProjectName}}
3. Homepage URL: http://localhost:3000
4. Callback URL: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/github
5. Click Register application
6. Copy Client ID into GITHUB_CLIENT_ID in .env.local
7. Click Generate a new client secret
8. Copy the secret into GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET in .env.local
{{end}}
