## Step 3 — Database setup

{{if .IsPrisma}}
### Run the migration

    npx prisma migrate dev --name init

This creates all required tables in your database:
User, Session, Account, Verification

### Verify in database browser

    npx prisma studio

Open http://localhost:5555 — you should see all 4 tables.

### Troubleshooting

If you get a connection error:
- Make sure your database server is running
- Check DATABASE_URL in .env.local is correct
- For SQLite: no server needed, the file is created automatically
- For PostgreSQL: make sure the database exists and credentials are correct
{{end}}
{{if .IsDrizzle}}
### Step 3a — Generate migration files

This reads your schema and creates SQL migration files:

    npx drizzle-kit generate

You will see a new folder created: drizzle/migrations/

### Step 3b — Apply migrations to the database

This runs the SQL files against your database and creates the tables:

    npx drizzle-kit migrate

### Step 3c — Verify in database browser

    npx drizzle-kit studio

Open https://local.drizzle.studio — you should see these tables:
user, session, account, verification

### Troubleshooting

If drizzle-kit migrate runs silently with no output:
- This means there are no pending migrations
- Run npx drizzle-kit generate first to create the migration files
- Then run npx drizzle-kit migrate again

If you get a connection refused error:
- Make sure your database server is running
- For XAMPP MySQL: open XAMPP Control Panel and start MySQL
- Check DATABASE_URL in .env — use 127.0.0.1 instead of localhost
  Example: DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:@127.0.0.1:3306/{{.ProjectName}}"
- Make sure the database exists — create it in phpMyAdmin if needed
- For PostgreSQL: make sure the database exists and the user has access

If migrate runs but tables are not visible in studio:
- Run generate first, then migrate
- Check that your DATABASE_URL points to the correct database
- Refresh the studio page after migration completes
{{end}}

