## Step 6 — Connect auth to your UI

The auth backend is fully wired. To use it in your components:

### Sign up a new user

    import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client";

    await authClient.signUp.email({
      email: "user@example.com",
      password: "password123",
      name: "John Doe",
    });

### Sign in

    await authClient.signIn.email({
      email: "user@example.com",
      password: "password123",
    });

### Sign out

    await authClient.signOut();

### Get the current session in a client component

    import { useSession } from "@/lib/auth-client";

    const { data: session, isPending } = useSession();
    // session.user.email, session.user.name, session.user.id

### Get the current session in a server component

    import { auth } from "@/lib/auth";
    import { headers } from "next/headers";

    const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() });

---
{{if .State}}
## Step 7 — Using Zustand

A user store is pre-configured at store/useUserStore.ts

    import { useUserStore } from "@/store/useUserStore";

    const { user, setUser, clearUser } = useUserStore();

Update the store after sign in:

    const { data } = await authClient.signIn.email({ ... });
    setUser(data.user);

Clear it after sign out:

    await authClient.signOut();
    clearUser();

